{"parse":{"title":"Varsity letter","pageid":378959,"revid":835567103,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Varsity_Letter.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/Varsity_Letter.png/220px-Varsity_Letter.png\" width=\"220\" height=\"164\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/Varsity_Letter.png/330px-Varsity_Letter.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/Varsity_Letter.png/440px-Varsity_Letter.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"959\" data-file-height=\"714\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Varsity_Letter.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Varsity letter awarded in the Arts (Lyre) and Academia (Lamp)</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>varsity letter</b> (or <b>monogram</b>) is an award earned in the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">United States</a> for excellence in school activities. A varsity letter signifies that its winner was a qualified <a href=\"/wiki/Varsity_team\" title=\"Varsity team\">varsity team</a> member, awarded after a certain standard was met.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Description\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Description</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Variations_and_application\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Variations and application</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Varsity_letter&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Description\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The award letter is usually made in the colors and initials representing the school that the recipient attends. The letter patch is primarily constructed of <a href=\"/wiki/Chenille_fabric\" title=\"Chenille fabric\">chenille</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Felt\" title=\"Felt\">felt</a> materials. Standard sizes range from 4 inches (102&#160;mm) to 8 inches (203&#160;mm). While 4 inches (102&#160;mm) and 5 inches (127&#160;mm) usually denote Junior Varsity achievements, 6 inches (152&#160;mm) to 8 inches (203&#160;mm) would denote full (Senior) Varsity. The stitching style used for creating the chenille look is called a moss stitch, while the outlining sew down is called a chain stitch.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Varsity_letter&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>With the advent of organized sports, there was a need for uniforms. There was an additional need for identifications which was satisfied by the use of emblems or letters.\n</p><p>In 1865, the <a href=\"/wiki/Harvard_University\" title=\"Harvard University\">Harvard</a> baseball team added an Old English 'H'. The 'H' was embroidered on the gray flannel shirt. The football team started to use the 'H' in 1875. For 25 years following the introduction in 1865 of the letter, it was the practice for the team captain to allow certain players who played in the most important games (Yale or Princeton) to keep the 'H' jerseys as an award. If a player did not play in an important game, the player had to return the jersey at the end of the season. Awarding the 'H' jersey may have been the birth of the varsity letter as an award. The letterman sweater was first regularly used by the 1891 \"Nine\" (baseball) and was black with a small Crimson 'H' on the left breast.\n</p><p>It is not known when the letter sweater came to high schools. The earliest known example of a letter sweater in a high school is found in the 1911 yearbook of Phoenix Union High School, Arizona Territory.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (December 2016)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> A student in a group photo is pictured, not in football uniform, wearing a <a href=\"/wiki/V-neck_sweater\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"V-neck sweater\">V-neck sweater</a> with the letter 'P' on the left side.\n</p><p>The sweater seems to be the home of the award letter from the 1890s until the 1930s. Another award during the 1920s and 1930s was a stadium style blanket given as an award. In the 1930s, the letter award started to appear on leather sleeved, wool-bodied jackets. The jackets from the 1930s were different in design than today's modern jacket.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Variations_and_application\">Variations and application</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Varsity_letter&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Variations and application\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>As a decorative clothing item, the varsity letter has a huge number of variations and no set standard is made to any school on how it should look.\n</p><p>Chenille letters come in many different forms and shapes. Some institutions use Old English or script style, two or three letter monogram, 3D shading, chenille bordered or the traditional straight block style. Students generally receive only one actual letter, but can win the distinction multiple times. These additional designations are shown by adding embroidered sport insignias, modeled metal insert pins, or bars that are attached to the letter. Some schools may embroider non-athletic letters with their award title, such as \"Academics\" or \"Arts\".\n</p>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-traditional\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:17.5px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:CV_Academic_Letter.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/CV_Academic_Letter.png/120px-CV_Academic_Letter.png\" width=\"120\" height=\"115\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/CV_Academic_Letter.png/180px-CV_Academic_Letter.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/CV_Academic_Letter.png/240px-CV_Academic_Letter.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"287\" data-file-height=\"275\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Two-letter monogram with embroidered academic insert\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:29px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:MNH_3_Letter_Monogram.gif\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a2/MNH_3_Letter_Monogram.gif/120px-MNH_3_Letter_Monogram.gif\" width=\"120\" height=\"92\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a2/MNH_3_Letter_Monogram.gif/180px-MNH_3_Letter_Monogram.gif 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a2/MNH_3_Letter_Monogram.gif/240px-MNH_3_Letter_Monogram.gif 2x\" data-file-width=\"360\" data-file-height=\"275\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Three-letter monogram\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:R_w_Warrior_Field_Hockey.gif\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/R_w_Warrior_Field_Hockey.gif/116px-R_w_Warrior_Field_Hockey.gif\" width=\"116\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/R_w_Warrior_Field_Hockey.gif/175px-R_w_Warrior_Field_Hockey.gif 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/R_w_Warrior_Field_Hockey.gif/233px-R_w_Warrior_Field_Hockey.gif 2x\" data-file-width=\"267\" data-file-height=\"275\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Chenille bordered letter with embroidered mascot and sport inserts\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:C_w_3D_Shading.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/C_w_3D_Shading.png/112px-C_w_3D_Shading.png\" width=\"112\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/C_w_3D_Shading.png/168px-C_w_3D_Shading.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/C_w_3D_Shading.png/223px-C_w_3D_Shading.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"256\" data-file-height=\"275\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Letter with 3D shading\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:21.5px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Traditional_Block_Letter_R_with_Embroidered_Mascot.gif\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/71/Traditional_Block_Letter_R_with_Embroidered_Mascot.gif/120px-Traditional_Block_Letter_R_with_Embroidered_Mascot.gif\" width=\"120\" height=\"107\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/71/Traditional_Block_Letter_R_with_Embroidered_Mascot.gif/180px-Traditional_Block_Letter_R_with_Embroidered_Mascot.gif 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/71/Traditional_Block_Letter_R_with_Embroidered_Mascot.gif/240px-Traditional_Block_Letter_R_with_Embroidered_Mascot.gif 2x\" data-file-width=\"400\" data-file-height=\"357\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Traditional block letter with embroidered mascot\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The chenille letter is traditionally placed on the left chest of the varsity jacket, which is also at times adorned with championship chenille patches showcasing the team or individual accomplishments. School mascot patches are also commonly used.\n</p><p>During the 1980s, and again in the 2010s, varsity jackets have been adopted into <a href=\"/wiki/Hip-hop_fashion\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hip-hop fashion\">hip-hop fashion</a>, with companies such as <a href=\"/wiki/Avirex\" title=\"Avirex\">Avirex</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Phat_farm\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Phat farm\">Phat Farm</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Rocawear\" title=\"Rocawear\">Rocawear</a> making their own variations.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Varsity_letter&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Letterman_(sports)\" title=\"Letterman (sports)\">Letterman (sports)</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Sporting_colours\" title=\"Sporting colours\">Sporting colours</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Varsity_letter&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20091017114347/http://members.cox.net/phxjer/sleeves/history.htm\">\"History of the Letter Award Tradition\"</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://members.cox.net/phxjer/sleeves/history.htm\">the original</a> on October 17, 2009.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=History+of+the+Letter+Award+Tradition&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmembers.cox.net%2Fphxjer%2Fsleeves%2Fhistory.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AVarsity+letter\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#c